    "body": "### Description\n\nHey ðŸ‘‹ \n\nI noticed this plugin has moved many configurations to the `lsp` runtime directory, which was not supported by the luarocks-tag-release workflow (which means luarocks and lux will not install the `lsp` directory as it is missing in the generated rockspec).\n\nI've [added support for the `lsp` runtime directory to the github action](https://github.com/nvim-neorocks/luarocks-tag-release/pull/643)\n\n@teto can you please delete the rockspec from luarocks.org (I think it's your account?) and rerun the workflow on the v2.0.0 tag?\nWe will need to do add `workflow_dispatch` to the triggers to rerun the workflow.\nOr, you could add `lsp` to the `copy_directories` list in the rockspec and upload it manually.",
